The paper discusses the challenges of tracking provenance in machine learning applications deployed in regulated environments, which involves tracking the data sources used for training ML models to the predictions of the deployed models. This problem is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), security and privacy (cs.CR), software engineering (cs.SE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the paper focuses on the technical aspects of tracking provenance in data science scripts, it is most likely to belong to cs.DB and cs.LG, which are the sub-categories that deal with data management and machine learning, respectively.
